SUMMARY:CoffeeTue- CO Trolley Line Coffee (28R) -- RSVP required
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Bicycle Club (LBC) Meetup\nRide Leader: Bruce Black\
 n\nCoffeeTue rides:\n• A rotating start location\, not a school\n• A p
 redetermined route\n• 25+/- mile routes\n• 13 to 15 mph average pace\n
 • Usually no sweep\n• “short” stop for refreshment/coffee mid-rout
 e at [Trolley Line Coffee](https://trolleylinecoffee.com/)\n\nClick for [R
 ide with GPS](https://routes.lancasterbikeclub.net/cue/co-trolley-line-cof
 fee-28r/)\n\nHelmets are mandatory. No ear buds. Please bring water and a 
 basic repair kit (spare tube\, tire levers\, pump/CO2 inflator).\n\nTo eli
 minate passing around a pen and paper waiver\, we require LBC Club members
 hip and Meetup RSVP below to join this ride.\n\nBeing on Meetup does not m
 ean you are a club member. [Join here](https://www.lancasterbikeclub.net/c
 ontent.aspx?page_id=60&club_id=257148).\n\nYour RSVP is your agreement to 
 abide by the club's [Code of Conduct](https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com
 /content.aspx?page_id=22&club_id=257148&module_id=323984) \,\n[Rules of th
 e Road](https://lancbikeclub.clubexpress.com/content.aspx?page_id=22&club_
